auguriis: see vi. 4, note on templa. The Augure formed the second Sacred College, and were originally three, one from each of the Romulean tribes. Later there were as many as sixteen. Their duty was to decide whether the gods favoured any undertaking or no, whether public or private. They derived most of their methods from the Etruscans.
